claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table of demographic characteristics and influenza vaccination history of study participants divided into four groups (n=122, 120, 283, 198), showing mean age, age groups, sex, race/ethnicity, study site, and receipt of prior influenza vaccines. does not support the claim because the table only presents participant demographics and vaccination history without any information on vaccine production methods, mutations, or effects on vaccine effectiveness Note: The table contains only demographic and prior vaccination data; it does not address mutation potential or effectiveness of egg- or cell-based vaccines.
